<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-19T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-19T22:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2213: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Neville</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-20T12:00:00+09:00">October 20,
                                1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 20—4:07
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>189. Department’s 181, October 3, 2 p.m. I have been informed orally by
                            the Foreign Office that the wireless station at Mukden is expected to be
                            in operation some time this week, with operators supplied by South
                            Manchuria Railway.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Neville</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>